commitResults.messageTitle: added the skeletal version of Duke that echos commands
added the ability to store inputs into a list and display the elements in the list
added the ability to mark tasks as done or not done
renamed duke to Candice and added functionality for ToDo, Deadline and Event
very slight edit to the response from candice
changed the java file name back to Duke and added test cases + their expected result
redid the logic flow to allow for the Action class to parse the input and create Action instances that can be resolved. Also added some new test cases
editing the exceptions slightly and adding a test case
Add the ability to save tasks locally
commitResults.messageBody:
Uses a text file to store the task list created during usage of the
program. Allows for task list to be reused after closing the program

commitResults.messageTitle: Use LocalDate and LocalTime instead of Strings for TimedTasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadline and Event tasks now use LocalDate which is compulsory and
LocalTime which is optional (set to null by default) instead of a
String to encapsulate the deadline timing

commitResults.messageTitle: Add minor adjustments to optimize code
commitResults.messageBody: removed unneeded import statements and methods

commitResults.messageTitle: Change logic flow of code to make it more object oriented
commitResults.messageBody:
Renamed Action to Command, created a CommandType Enum class, created
Storage, Paraser and Ui classes for a more object oriented code.
Still need to touch up on object oriented approach of the Duke class.

Added packages to the files (candice, candice.command, candice.exception
and candice.task)

Added test classes for every main class with public methods and added
test cases for the Task and TimedTask classes
Added javadocs for Parser and CommandType

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix small bugs in the code
commitResults.messageBody:
Changed the storage description and test cases of the event class as
it was falsely returning and checking the event class as a deadline
class.
